sql:
SELECT area_id, COUNT(condition_id) AS condition_count
FROM area_conditions
GROUP BY area_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_non_compliant_conditions
FROM area_conditions
WHERE status = 'non-compliant';

external_knowledge:
'safety' and 'environmental' are categories of changes; 
Areas without any changes will be included in the results, possibly showing a zero or NULL average change count;
Safety changes might include things like repairing hazardous conditions, while environmental changes could involve actions to reduce pollution.

; Non-compliant conditions refer to conditions that do not meet certain standards or regulations; 
; Targets refer to specific goals that areas are supposed to achieve; 'not achieved' targets are those that have not been met; 
; Background changes refer to changes made to the area that are not directly related to condition checks or target achievements.
